cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving search quality in enterprise email search, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) in computer science. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel application of Maximum Mean Discrepancy (MMD) approach to IR, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning and neural networks. This makes cs.CL and cs.LG likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper addresses the challenge of limited data in smaller institutions, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (AI) research, making cs.AI a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experiments with large-scale data, which is often associated with computer vision (CV) research, making cs.CV a less likely but still possible sub-category.
